        <page n="02" image="pa.fr.vs.1861.10.09.02">
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Are You Ready?</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"The cry of 'no party' is one of the most flimsy devices of the enemy to
                    gull the people, whilst this and other schemes are continually prated around by
                    the Republican party; they are at this time more intensely and uncompromisingly
                    partisan than they have been in the past."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Encourages Democratic voters to vote in the upcoming election and not to
                    abandon the Democratic Party.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Look out for Them</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Nill</ln>
                        <fn>James</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Reilly</ln>
                        <fn>Wilson</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Warns that Democrats should not be deceived by the Republicans and should
                    cast their votes for Reilly.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>The Judgeship of our District</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Reilly</ln>
                        <fn>Wilson</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Nill</ln>
                        <fn>James</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Endorses Reilly over Nill.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <pageNote>Numerous articles encouraging Democrats to vote and endorsing the Democratic
                ticket.</pageNote>
        </page>
        <page n="03" image="pa.fr.vs.1861.10.09.03">
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>The Pennsylvania Volunteers and the Election</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Reports provisions established to enable soldiers to vote.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Who Encourages the South?</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"The Republicans say to the Southern Union men they shall have no further
                    guarantees of their rights, and those they have already will not be further
                    respected than events render necessary."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Asserts that Republicans encourage the rebellion by making it appear as
                    though they have allies and sympathy from Northern Democrats while refusing to
                    ensure the rights of the states.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <pageNote/>
        </page>
        <page n="04" image="pa.fr.vs.1861.10.09.04">
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Voters Remember</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"The Voters of all parties should remember that the names of Democrats
                    placed upon the Republican ticket are those of disappointed, broken-down
                    political hacks."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Warns Democrats and Republicans alike not to be fooled by the Republican
                    ticket.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>A Lie Nailed</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Lesher</ln>
                        <fn>Christian D.</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Accuses an editorialist of lying about Lesher's remarks at a Middleburg
                    meeting.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Can't be Caught</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Duncan</ln>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Hamsher</ln>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Armstrong</ln>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Asserts that Democrats can't be caught in the Republican-backed Union
                    ticket trap.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>The Mongrel Ticket</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Nill</ln>
                        <fn>James</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Rowe</ln>
                        <fn>John</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Nitterhouse</ln>
                        <fn>John</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Wuderlich</ln>
                        <fn>D.K.</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Denounces the "mongrel ticket" of former Democrats fielded by the
                    Republican party.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Will a True Prophet be an Inconsistent Politician</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"A Vote for Abraham Lincoln is a vote in favor of Negro equality, in favor
                    of placing a drunken, degraded, worthless black on an equal footing with
                    yourself."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Nill</ln>
                        <fn>James</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Accuses Nill of inconsistency because he previously denounced Republicans
                    as abolitionists but has now joined them. Item quotes a previous Nill diatribe
                    against Lincoln as proof.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>5</column>
                <head>Home Again</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Eyster</ln>
                        <fn>J. Allison</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Reports that J. Allison Eyster has been freed by the Confederates and has
                    returned home. He appears to be in good health.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>6</column>
                <head>The Legislative Ticket</head>
                <origin>Fulton Democrat</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
